# ✅ Experiment 2 – Dockerize Flask App + Push Docker Hub

## Aim:

To containerize Flask application using Docker.

## app.py

```python id="q2c1"
from flask import Flask
app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route('/')
def home():
    return "Hello from Dockerized Flask!"

app.run(host='0.0.0.0', port=5000)
```

## requirements.txt

```txt id="q2c2"
flask
```

## Dockerfile

```dockerfile id="q2c3"
FROM python:3.11-slim
WORKDIR /app
COPY requirements.txt .
RUN pip install -r requirements.txt
COPY . .
EXPOSE 5000
CMD ["python","app.py"]
```

## Commands:

```bash id="q2c4"
docker build -t username/flask-app .
docker run -p 5000:5000 username/flask-app
docker login
docker push username/flask-app
```

## Expected Output:

Open browser:

```text id="q2c5"
http://localhost:5000
```

Shows:

```text id="q2c6"
Hello from Dockerized Flask!
```

